00:42:04.780 --> 00:42:07.090
I have to teach you
quickly on this.

00:42:07.090 --> 00:42:10.650
And I know that
the USA and Canada

00:42:10.650 --> 00:42:13.930
have very parallel histories,
because I researched it.

00:42:13.930 --> 00:42:19.070
And I'm not saying I'm an
expert in the US law, I'm not.

00:42:19.070 --> 00:42:22.630
I am a lawyer in the
Canadian common law system,

00:42:22.630 --> 00:42:25.740
and I'm primarily a researcher.

00:42:25.740 --> 00:42:29.780
So the Doctrine of Discovery
is under the umbrella

00:42:29.780 --> 00:42:33.640
of the Manifest Destiny
[INAUDIBLE] indigenous peoples.

00:42:33.640 --> 00:42:37.040
The original peoples were
considered the flora and fauna,

00:42:37.040 --> 00:42:39.320
we're not human.

00:42:39.320 --> 00:42:41.200
We are not human.

00:42:41.200 --> 00:42:43.870
I say that over, and over
again, because that's

00:42:43.870 --> 00:42:49.380
what rolls out in every policy
and law that we see today.

00:42:49.380 --> 00:42:50.400
Today.

00:42:50.400 --> 00:42:52.220
And I want the young
people to know,

00:42:52.220 --> 00:42:55.430
and I want the
indigenous women to know,

00:42:55.430 --> 00:42:59.320
that this system targets you
as the most marginalized,

00:42:59.320 --> 00:43:01.380
and the most hated.

00:43:01.380 --> 00:43:06.050
And I am very blunt because I
don't have time for niceties.

00:43:06.050 --> 00:43:12.950
Christian monarchs at that
time worked with Pope Alexander

00:43:12.950 --> 00:43:17.890
in creating, from the
imaginations of men,

00:43:17.890 --> 00:43:23.550
from the imaginations of a
pope, a Doctrine of Discovery.

00:43:23.550 --> 00:43:26.040
And it's exactly the
same here for you,

00:43:26.040 --> 00:43:28.210
except you had Columbus.

00:43:28.210 --> 00:43:32.540
We had John Cabot, The Explorer.

00:43:32.540 --> 00:43:38.430
So John Cabot came across
the ocean with instruments,

00:43:38.430 --> 00:43:41.140
and when he arrived,
and these instruments

00:43:41.140 --> 00:43:46.800
were the charters directed from
the pope-- OK, from the pope.

00:43:46.800 --> 00:43:50.650
And when he arrived here
he did a Christian chant.

00:43:50.650 --> 00:43:54.810
The very first thing he did when
he landed on Original People's

00:43:54.810 --> 00:44:00.940
soil, he got off his
boat, went to our lands,

00:44:00.940 --> 00:44:04.590
took instruments that he
carried across the ocean,

00:44:04.590 --> 00:44:07.520
and did a very-- the very
first act that he did

00:44:07.520 --> 00:44:11.320
was a Christian chant, and
he put that instrument deep

00:44:11.320 --> 00:44:14.790
in the soil of our
people's lands,

00:44:14.790 --> 00:44:21.560
and he baptized our lands for
the sovereign, for the pope.

00:44:21.560 --> 00:44:28.620
That's a very symbolic
Christian and sovereign act

00:44:28.620 --> 00:44:31.070
of those nations
across the ocean,

00:44:31.070 --> 00:44:35.000
and very important for us today.

00:44:35.000 --> 00:44:40.320
At that moment, when he did
that, the presumed sovereignty

00:44:40.320 --> 00:44:44.410
of the monarch, the presumed
sovereignty on our side

00:44:44.410 --> 00:44:46.110
was the British rule.

00:44:46.110 --> 00:44:50.900
It was crystallized, as
they say in law, right?

00:44:50.900 --> 00:44:53.590
Crystallized at that moment.

00:44:53.590 --> 00:44:56.470
This is the timeline.

00:44:56.470 --> 00:44:59.250
So before that, the
Original Peoples

00:44:59.250 --> 00:45:06.880
lived in independent, powerful
societies governed by our laws,

00:45:06.880 --> 00:45:13.020
the original instructions
given to us by our [INAUDIBLE],

00:45:13.020 --> 00:45:16.160
or for other
nations, however you

00:45:16.160 --> 00:45:21.900
choose to call your
spiritual entities.

00:45:21.900 --> 00:45:24.870
With my people we call
him [NON-ENGLISH],

00:45:24.870 --> 00:45:29.550
our original instructions,
vibrant, beautiful.

00:45:29.550 --> 00:45:32.940
And when the Doctrine
of Christian Discovery

00:45:32.940 --> 00:45:36.350
was applied in 1497,
the crystallization

00:45:36.350 --> 00:45:40.310
of their presumed sovereignty
rolled out onto our lands,

00:45:40.310 --> 00:45:44.320
without our knowledge,
without our consent.

00:45:44.320 --> 00:45:48.080
And then a series of events
happened from that moment on,

00:45:48.080 --> 00:45:52.930
the Royal Proclamation,
in the 1700s, consolidated

00:45:52.930 --> 00:45:56.680
with the Doctrine of
Discovery, consolidated

00:45:56.680 --> 00:46:00.530
with the Doctrine of
Discovery, and they took us

00:46:00.530 --> 00:46:03.800
under their wing because
we were not human.

00:46:03.800 --> 00:46:11.500
We became wards of this colonial
state, and we are not human.

00:46:11.500 --> 00:46:16.290
And at that moment, when we
were taken under their wing,

00:46:16.290 --> 00:46:20.977
we see a lot of colonial
policies and laws

00:46:20.977 --> 00:46:21.810
coming out of there.

00:46:21.810 --> 00:46:27.200
We hear the language, fiduciary,
trust-like, coming out

00:46:27.200 --> 00:46:28.960
of there.

00:46:28.960 --> 00:46:31.370
And it's because
we're not human.

00:46:31.370 --> 00:46:34.210
I keep repeating
that because that's

00:46:34.210 --> 00:46:38.190
what comes out of these
court cases, the Indian Act,

00:46:38.190 --> 00:46:40.420
and everything that
we're hearing today.

00:46:43.220 --> 00:46:47.910
Then something else happened,
Johnson versus M'Intosh,

00:46:47.910 --> 00:46:51.220
in 1923, came out
of here, and then

00:46:51.220 --> 00:46:54.150
Canada took it, and
applied it over there.

00:46:54.150 --> 00:46:59.530
And then became a
series of case law

00:46:59.530 --> 00:47:02.530
that said we were
parasitic on the underlying

00:47:02.530 --> 00:47:05.710
title of the crown.

00:47:05.710 --> 00:47:08.200
The underlying
title of the crown

00:47:08.200 --> 00:47:11.700
is the Doctrine of Discovery.

00:47:11.700 --> 00:47:13.620
You need to understand that.

00:47:13.620 --> 00:47:16.370
The Doctrine of Discovery,
in this case law,

00:47:16.370 --> 00:47:20.410
has been disguised at the
underlying title of the crown.

00:47:20.410 --> 00:47:25.910
It's a myth, and a lie
told over, and over again,

00:47:25.910 --> 00:47:28.460
every time we go to court.

00:47:28.460 --> 00:47:33.490
Every time we go to court
they apply the underlying

00:47:33.490 --> 00:47:36.980
title of the crown, which
is a myth, and a lie,

00:47:36.980 --> 00:47:40.950
from the imaginations of
men who brought it here.

00:47:43.480 --> 00:47:48.520
From there, in Canada, they
created the British North

00:47:48.520 --> 00:47:51.900
America Act, and
they took our lands,

00:47:51.900 --> 00:47:56.860
instantly condemning
us into poverty,

00:47:56.860 --> 00:47:59.990
instantly making them wealthy.

00:47:59.990 --> 00:48:04.830
Because in [? 9124 ?] they
took our lands, lands,

00:48:04.830 --> 00:48:08.960
and Indian lands
reserved for Indians,

00:48:08.960 --> 00:48:12.110
instantly condemning
us into poverty.

00:48:12.110 --> 00:48:15.220
A direct connection to
the Doctrine of Discovery,

00:48:15.220 --> 00:48:19.520
because as human
beings, as non-humans,

00:48:19.520 --> 00:48:24.730
as non-human beings,
we cannot own property.

00:48:24.730 --> 00:48:32.620
We had no laws, we were
barbarians, savages.

00:48:32.620 --> 00:48:35.520
And then from there they
created the Indian Act,

00:48:35.520 --> 00:48:38.980
and then from there
the number of treaties.

00:48:38.980 --> 00:48:41.600
Think about that.

00:48:41.600 --> 00:48:45.240
The treaties were
created on the notion

00:48:45.240 --> 00:48:48.390
that our lands have
already been taken.

00:48:48.390 --> 00:48:50.530
All of our resources
have already

00:48:50.530 --> 00:48:54.580
been taken by the
Doctrine of Discovery,

00:48:54.580 --> 00:48:57.850
by the underlying
title of the crown.

00:48:57.850 --> 00:49:01.720
And then from there,
today, even in the US,

00:49:01.720 --> 00:49:04.540
I see that language,
the language

00:49:04.540 --> 00:49:09.900
that they used in calling
us stakeholders, occupiers.

00:49:09.900 --> 00:49:12.310
And then we see the
land claims process

00:49:12.310 --> 00:49:20.330
that we have to go to their
artificial illegal system

00:49:20.330 --> 00:49:22.390
to gain back our lands.

00:49:22.390 --> 00:49:24.970
How ridiculous is that?

00:49:24.970 --> 00:49:28.390
How awful is that?

00:49:28.390 --> 00:49:31.820
And then we see the
Treaty Land Entitlement,

00:49:31.820 --> 00:49:34.480
Indian residential schools.

00:49:34.480 --> 00:49:36.680
You know what the Indian
residential schools did?

00:49:36.680 --> 00:49:39.800
And I'm sure they did
the very same thing here.

00:49:39.800 --> 00:49:42.410
We have something in
a number of treaties,

00:49:42.410 --> 00:49:45.410
and I'm from Treaty 6,
and I've researched this.

00:49:45.410 --> 00:49:48.900
I even wrote a book called,
Nationhood Interrupted,

00:49:48.900 --> 00:49:52.260
Revitalizing Nehiyaw
Legal Systems,

00:49:52.260 --> 00:49:56.240
and I talk about
this in chapter 4.

00:49:56.240 --> 00:49:59.660
And I talk about a treaty
term and promise, where, and

00:49:59.660 --> 00:50:05.610
I'm quoting from the treaty
negotiations, where it says,

00:50:05.610 --> 00:50:09.310
for a family of-- one square
mile, for a family of five,

00:50:09.310 --> 00:50:11.230
more or less.

00:50:11.230 --> 00:50:16.160
I have seven children,
eight, including myself.

00:50:16.160 --> 00:50:19.570
I'm supposed to be entitled,
by that treaty term

00:50:19.570 --> 00:50:23.280
and promise, a one square mile.

00:50:23.280 --> 00:50:24.990
I have yet to see that.

00:50:24.990 --> 00:50:28.190
It's my dream in my lifetime
that the treaty term

00:50:28.190 --> 00:50:31.030
and promise will be fulfilled.

00:50:31.030 --> 00:50:32.470
But what happened
at the time when

00:50:32.470 --> 00:50:36.890
Indian residential schools,
when they came for the children?

00:50:36.890 --> 00:50:40.110
How was the fastest way
to prevent a treaty term

00:50:40.110 --> 00:50:43.090
and promise from
being fulfilled?

00:50:43.090 --> 00:50:43.940
Was the fastest way?

00:50:43.940 --> 00:50:46.420
Anyone guess?

00:50:46.420 --> 00:50:48.900
You take the children.

00:50:48.900 --> 00:50:54.320
You can no longer meet the
criteria of a family, right.

00:50:54.320 --> 00:50:57.240
You take the children.

00:50:57.240 --> 00:51:01.990
In total violation
of what we thought

00:51:01.990 --> 00:51:05.770
was an authentic treaty.

00:51:05.770 --> 00:51:08.050
And then you see
the conversations

00:51:08.050 --> 00:51:11.570
about self-government.

00:51:11.570 --> 00:51:17.460
And during this era
we see the Indian Act.

00:51:17.460 --> 00:51:20.070
And right away, the first
language you see is,

00:51:20.070 --> 00:51:22.700
an Indian woman cannot vote.

00:51:22.700 --> 00:51:24.910
And Indian woman
will lose her status

00:51:24.910 --> 00:51:28.120
if she marries a non-Indian man.

00:51:28.120 --> 00:51:35.680
The target of women was
insidious, insidious.

00:51:35.680 --> 00:51:41.000
In 1670 the Jesuits came
looking for my people,

00:51:41.000 --> 00:51:43.410
indigenous nehiyaw people.

00:51:43.410 --> 00:51:46.380
And they found them
in the James Bay Area.

00:51:46.380 --> 00:51:49.660
And if you see the
journals of the Jesuits,

00:51:49.660 --> 00:51:53.980
right away they
say, the Cree women

00:51:53.980 --> 00:51:57.800
have far too much
authority and jurisdiction.

00:51:57.800 --> 00:52:00.020
We have to eliminate that.

00:52:00.020 --> 00:52:05.090
It took them a long time,
but they became successful.

00:52:05.090 --> 00:52:09.370
Today our matrilineal
societies are so decimated,

00:52:09.370 --> 00:52:13.855
they're a mere shadow
of what they should be.

00:52:13.855 --> 00:52:18.120
What they should be,
they're a shadow of it.

00:52:18.120 --> 00:52:21.610
Another thing happened,
as they were working

00:52:21.610 --> 00:52:25.960
to dismantle and abolish the
authority of indigenous women,

00:52:25.960 --> 00:52:30.060
the Original Peoples'
jurisdiction,

00:52:30.060 --> 00:52:32.690
they began to target the women.

00:52:32.690 --> 00:52:38.200
In the Indian Act they targeted
the birthright to determine who

00:52:38.200 --> 00:52:43.090
their citizens are by
legislating who they can marry

00:52:43.090 --> 00:52:45.460
and who they cannot.

00:52:45.460 --> 00:52:48.900
And another thing-- I'm
not for voting, by the way,

00:52:48.900 --> 00:52:53.060
and I'll tell you why
in two minutes or less.

00:52:53.060 --> 00:52:55.360
[LAUGHTER]

00:52:55.360 --> 00:53:01.720
So, women, under the Indian
Act, were not allowed to vote,

00:53:01.720 --> 00:53:05.260
nor were they allowed
to run for leadership.

00:53:05.260 --> 00:53:08.210
And when that ended
about, between 1940--

00:53:08.210 --> 00:53:12.230
and there's debate
in that-- into 1960,

00:53:12.230 --> 00:53:15.580
another thing happened, they
rolled out the traplines,

00:53:15.580 --> 00:53:18.850
from 1945, to what we see today.

00:53:18.850 --> 00:53:23.560
And the traplines are
anywhere, from 95% to 98%,

00:53:23.560 --> 00:53:24.803
under the men's names.

00:53:27.440 --> 00:53:31.450
The women in my nation have
jurisdiction and authority

00:53:31.450 --> 00:53:34.760
over land and water, because
we carry the water ceremonies.

00:53:34.760 --> 00:53:36.640
We carry them.

00:53:36.640 --> 00:53:42.010
That has been decimated under
this Doctrine of Discovery.

00:53:42.010 --> 00:53:44.170
All of us need to
understand, we have

00:53:44.170 --> 00:53:50.450
to work collectively and be
very strong in abolishing

00:53:50.450 --> 00:53:52.000
the Doctrine of Discovery.

00:53:52.000 --> 00:53:53.370
And what will that mean?

00:53:53.370 --> 00:53:54.510
I don't know.

00:53:54.510 --> 00:53:56.880
I'm not sure because
I'm still researching.

00:53:56.880 --> 00:53:58.470
This is relatively new to me.

00:53:58.470 --> 00:54:01.290
I was blown away when I
was going to law school.

00:54:01.290 --> 00:54:05.050
Why weren't we not told that
the underlying title was

00:54:05.050 --> 00:54:08.240
the Doctrine of Discovery?

00:54:08.240 --> 00:54:13.900
When we go, and I say this
with all respect, and kindness,

00:54:13.900 --> 00:54:17.770
and I know it's-- I'm not
here to offend anyone,

00:54:17.770 --> 00:54:21.660
nor to demean your work--
but when we go to vote

00:54:21.660 --> 00:54:24.620
in their systems, or to
run in their systems,

00:54:24.620 --> 00:54:29.010
we entrench them, and
we legitimize them,

00:54:29.010 --> 00:54:32.320
when we should be
stepping away, and saying,

00:54:32.320 --> 00:54:40.580
you do not have authority to
be putting this system out that

00:54:40.580 --> 00:54:45.790
dehumanizes women, that
marginalizes women,

00:54:45.790 --> 00:54:49.700
continues the patriarchy
and the misogyny,

00:54:49.700 --> 00:54:52.480
especially on indigenous women.

00:54:52.480 --> 00:54:54.010
We have missing
or murdered women

00:54:54.010 --> 00:55:00.460
in Canada, the official
numbers, approximately 1,300.

00:55:00.460 --> 00:55:05.650
The unofficial number
is approximately 4,000.

00:55:05.650 --> 00:55:10.700
In my own family, my brother
was murdered, two of my aunties

00:55:10.700 --> 00:55:12.840
were murdered.

00:55:12.840 --> 00:55:15.700
And that's not a unique story.

00:55:15.700 --> 00:55:19.635
Every indigenous family that you
talk to, this is their story.

00:55:22.160 --> 00:55:26.020
We have to change that story.

00:55:26.020 --> 00:55:31.870
We need to believe and
envision a time of freedom

00:55:31.870 --> 00:55:35.940
for indigenous people,
because we do not have it.

00:55:35.940 --> 00:55:37.540
We do not have it.

00:55:37.540 --> 00:55:39.770
Not as long as the
Doctrine of Discovery

00:55:39.770 --> 00:55:43.180
still applies as the
underlying title, giving

00:55:43.180 --> 00:55:49.350
jurisdiction to the colonizer
in an illegal imagining,

00:55:49.350 --> 00:55:51.900
coming from it.

00:55:51.900 --> 00:56:00.160
I want a dream, I have a dream,
that some day, in my lifetime,

00:56:00.160 --> 00:56:05.560
I will see my grandchildren
born in freedom and liberation,

00:56:05.560 --> 00:56:07.260
and self-determination.

00:56:07.260 --> 00:56:09.161
That's my dream.

00:56:09.161 --> 00:56:10.036
[NON-ENGLISH SPEECH].

00:56:18.030 --> 00:56:20.570
I speak my language
today because something

00:56:20.570 --> 00:56:24.070
happened that's very unique.

00:56:24.070 --> 00:56:27.040
My great grandmother didn't
go to residential school.

00:56:27.040 --> 00:56:30.560
When the Indian agent and the
priest came for the children,

00:56:30.560 --> 00:56:35.660
they were hidden away deep
in the forests of my people.

00:56:35.660 --> 00:56:39.780
My grandmother, same thing,
my mother same thing--

00:56:39.780 --> 00:56:41.970
hidden away.

00:56:41.970 --> 00:56:44.430
With me, same
thing, hidden away.

00:56:44.430 --> 00:56:46.320
I'm grateful for that today.

00:56:46.320 --> 00:56:49.860
Speak my language.
[NON-ENGLISH SPEECH].

